"Sterken C.","Ernst Julius Öpik, solar variability and climate change",2011,"Baltic Astronomy","20","2",,"195","203",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-81555199712&partnerID=40&md5=c9bf6497e17aa9336e194d47b11be759","Vrije Univtrsiteit Brussel, Pleinlaan 2, Brussels, B-1050, Belgium","Sterken, C., Vrije Univtrsiteit Brussel, Pleinlaan 2, Brussels, B-1050, Belgium","This paper covers some aspects of the life and work of the Estonian astronomer Ernst Opik (1893-1985), who contributed to a very wide range of astronomical disciplines, and whose publications span more than 70 years. He worked in Estonia, the Soviet Union, the United States, Germany and Northern Ireland. His visions on the role of solar variability in global climate change are emphasized, and his opinions on modelling in science are explained, in addition to his views about scientific refereeing and publishing.","Earth: Climate change; History of astronomy; Sun: Variability",,,,,,,"Imbrie, J., Imbrie, J.Z., (1980) Science, 207, p. 943; Leppik, L., (2011) Tartu Tähetorn, , Tallinn, Estonia: Aasta Raamat; Milankovitch, M., Mathematische klimalehre und astronomische theorie der klimaschwankungen (1930) Handbuch der Klimatologie, , Band 1, Teil A; Öpik, E.J., (1953) Contrib. Armagh Obs., (9); Öpik, E.J., (1976) Science, 191, p. 1292; Öpik, E.J., (1977) ARA&A, 15, p. 1; Solanki, S.K., Usoskin, I.G., Kromer, B., (2004) Nature, 431, p. 1084; Sterken, C., (1969) Invloed van de Seculaire Variaties van de Baanelementen Derplan-eten Op het Mathematisch Klimaat van de Planeet Mars, , MSc thesis, Universiteit Gent, Ghent, Belgium; Van Den Heuvel, E.P.J., Buurman, P., (1974) Marine Geology and Oceanography of the Arctic Seas, , Chap. 15, Springer; Van Der Kruit, P.C., Van Berkel, K., The legacy of J. C. Kapteyn (2000) Astrophysics and Space Science Library, 246. , Kluwer","Sterken, C.; Vrije Univtrsiteit Brussel, Pleinlaan 2, Brussels, B-1050, Belgium",,,,,,,,13920049,,,,"English","Baltic Astron.",Ar